track_notes: This is a path connecting Rudnik village, Ostrvica YU/CS-033, and State road 22 (Ibarska magistrala). The road is asphalted. Distance from East (Rudnik village) is 6.3 km, and distance from State road 22 is 4 km (this part is narrow and difficult to navigate without gps track). Waypoint CS033_walk is at the start of the trail to the summit. Finding a place to park might be difficult because there is no designated parking space. There are no water springs either.

This is a short (900 m long and 220 m up) walk to the summit of Ostrvica YU/CS-033. The summit is of volcanic origin and quite prominent from distance.
There path is marked, and closer to the top there are handrails installed on slightly exposed parts. The rocks might be slippery if wet. Beware of venomous vipers during spring and summer. The summit top is flat, narrow and 20 m long.
